The paper discusses the use of multiple measures to characterize the performance of different algorithms in complex optimization tasks. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to optimization, machine learning, and robotics. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely sub-category as the paper specifically discusses the use of the MAP-Elites algorithm for evolving robot controller repertoires. 

cs.RO (Robotics) is also a likely sub-category as the paper focuses on analyzing the search performance across different robot morphologies. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of multiple measures to evaluate the performance of different algorithms. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the use of ordinal effect sizes and Pareto dominance to analyze complex optimization tasks. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely sub-category but still possible as the paper discusses the evolution of robot controller repertoires and the analysis of search performance across different robot morphologies.
